-----------
| texgen2 |
-----------

This folder contains texgen2, the successor of texgen. Texgen2 is used to place
different texture types on a heightfield. It can use inputs like slope or perlin
noise to decide which texture type to place.

---------
| Usage |
---------

texgen [parameters]
parameters:
  -s or --script file.texgen    Load file.texgen as script
  -i or --infile file.tga:u:v   Load file.tga to position (u,v)
                                It is possible to load multiple height fields
                                using multiple instances of this parameter.
                                Not using it at all is also possible, which will
                                result in height 0 for all points.
  -o or --outfile file.tga      Save output file to file.tga
  -w or --width                 Set output image width
  -h or --height                Set output image height
  -u or --usage or --help       Display this information

------------
| Examples |
------------

See the examples folder for some hints how to write scripts.

